Rating: 0
I made quite a number of changes so please read this as a suggestion rather than a true review of the recipe. I used chicken breast instead of a whole chicken, red pepper flakes instead of chilli powder and cornflour instead of normal flour. I wasn't sure how the butter, chili and flour mixture could be easily spread over the chicken so I melted the butter in a pan over low heat instead and poured it over the chicken breast. Next I seasoned it with the red chili flakes, salt and some sugar and pepper. I turned the chicken a bit to coat it more evenly. Next I dusted it with the cornflour and again turned it to coat it evenly. I roasted the chicken breast for about 30 minutes at 180 degree celcius (slightly less than 375 degree Fahrenheit) with the garlic cloves. Despite the various changes, it turned out pretty delicious and crispy on the outside. I may even reduce cooking time slightly.

