Very good recipe as written. One important thing that I'll do differently next time is to remove the bird from the fridge and allow time to take some of the chill off before applying the chili/butter mixture. I am very aware of the salmonella risk so I'm not talking room temp here. Because the chicken was so cold, the mixture solidified and didn't spread very well. Definitely deglaze the fond on the bottom of your roaster to use in the gravy. Great with any potato side dish.

